  92,11,And his money will not avail him when he plummets
  92,12,It is upon Us to guide
  92,13,And to Us belong the Last and the First
  92,14,I have warned you of a Fierce Blaze
  92,15,None will burn in it except the very wicked
  92,16,He who denies and turns away
  92,17,But the devout will avoid it
  92,18,He who gives his money to become pure
  92,19,Seeking no favor in return
  92,20,"Only seeking the acceptance of his Lord, the Most High"
  92,21,And he will be satisfied
  93,1,By the morning light
  93,2,And the night as it settles
  93,3,"Your Lord did not abandon you, nor did He forget"
  93,4,The Hereafter is better for you than the First
  93,5,"And your Lord will give you, and you will be satisfied"
  93,6,"Did He not find you orphaned, and sheltered you"
  93,7,"And found you wandering, and guided you"
  93,8,"And found you in need, and enriched you"
  93,9,"Therefore, do not mistreat the orphan"
  93,10,Nor rebuff the seeker
  93,11,But proclaim the blessings of your Lord
  94,1,Did We not soothe your heart
  94,2,And lift from you your burden
  94,3,Which weighed down your back
  94,4,And raised for you your reputation
  94,5,With hardship comes ease
  94,6,With hardship comes ease
  94,7,"When your work is done, turn to devotion"
  94,8,And to your Lord turn for everything
  95,1,By the fig and the olive
  95,2,And Mount Sinai
  95,3,And this safe land
  95,4,We created man in the best design
  95,5,Then reduced him to the lowest of the low
  95,6,Except those who believe and do righteous deeds; for them is a reward without end
  95,7,So why do you still reject the religion
  95,8,Is God not the Wisest of the wise
  96,1,"Read: In the Name of your Lord who created"
  96,2,Created man from a clot
  96,3,"Read: And your Lord is the Most Generous"
  96,4,He who taught by the pen
  96,5,Taught man what he never knew
  96,6,"In fact, man oversteps all bounds"
  96,7,When he considers himself exempt
  96,8,But to your Lord is the return
  96,9,Have you seen him who prevents
  96,10,A servant when he prays
  96,11,Do you think he is upon guidance
  96,12,Or advocates righteousness
  96,13,Do you see how he disbelieved and turned away
  96,14,Does he not know that God sees
  96,15,"No. If he does not desist, We will drag him by the forelock"
  96,16,"A deceitful, sinful forelock"
  96,17,Let him call on his gang
  96,18,We will call the Guards
  96,19,"No, do not obey him; but kneel down, and come near"
  97,1,We sent it down on the Night of Decree
  97,2,But what will convey to you what the Night of Decree is
  97,3,The Night of Decree is better than a thousand months
  97,4,"In it descend the angels and the Spirit, by the leave of their Lord, with every command"
  97,5,Peace it is; until the rise of dawn
  98,1,"Those who disbelieved among the People of the Scripture, and the Polytheists, were not apart, until the Clear Evidence came to them"
  98,2,A messenger from God reciting purified scripts
  98,3,In them are valuable writings
  98,4,"Those who were given the Scripture did not splinter, except after the Clear Evidence came to them"
  98,5,"They were commanded only to worship God, devoting their faith to Him alone, and to practice regular prayer, and to give alms. That is the upright religion"
  98,6,"Those who disbelieve among the People of the Scripture, and the Polytheists, will be in the Fire of Hell, where they will abide forever. These are the worst of creatures"
  98,7,As for those who believe and lead a righteous life—these are the best of creatures
  98,8,"Their reward is with their Lord: Gardens of Eternity beneath which rivers flow, where they will abide forever. God is pleased with them, and they are pleased with Him. That is for whoever fears His Lord"
  99,1,When the earth is shaken with its quake
  99,2,And the earth brings out its loads
  99,3,"And man says, 'What is the matter with it"
  99,4,"On that Day, it will tell its tales"
  99,5,For your Lord will have inspired it
  99,6,"On that Day, the people will emerge in droves, to be shown their works"
  99,7,Whoever has done an atom's weight of good will see it
  99,8,And whoever has done an atom's weight of evil will see it
  100,1,By the racers panting
  100,2,Igniting sparks
  100,3,Raiding at dawn
  100,4,Raising clouds of dust
  100,5,Storming into the midst
  100,6,"Indeed, the human being is ungrateful to his Lord"
  100,7,And he bears witness to that
  100,8,And he is fierce in his love of wealth
  100,9,Does he not know? When the contents of the graves are scattered around
  100,10,And the contents of the hearts are obtained
  100,11,"Their Lord, on that Day, is fully informed of them"
  101,1,The Shocker
  101,2,What is the Shocker
  101,3,What will explain to you what the Shocker is
  101,4,The Day when the people will be like scattered moths
  101,5,And the mountains will be like tufted wool
  101,6,As for he whose scales are heavy
  101,7,He will be in a pleasant life
  101,8,But as for he whose scales are light
  101,9,His home is the Abyss
  101,10,Do you know what it is
  101,11,A Raging Fire
  102,1,Abundance distracts you
  102,2,Until you visit the graveyards
  102,3,"Indeed, you will know"
  102,4,"Certainly, you will know"
  102,5,If you knew with knowledge of certainty
  102,6,You would see the Inferno
  102,7,Then you will see it with the eye of certainty
  102,8,"Then, on that Day, you will be questioned about the Bliss"
  103,1,By time
  103,2,The human being is in loss
  103,3,"Except those who believe, and do good works, and encourage truth, and recommend patience"
  104,1,Woe to every slanderer backbiter
  104,2,Who gathers wealth and counts it over
  104,3,Thinking that his wealth has made him immortal
  104,4,By no means. He will be thrown into the Crusher
  104,5,And what will make you realize what the Crusher is
  104,6,God's kindled Fire
  104,7,That laps to the hearts
  104,8,It closes in on them
  104,9,In extended columns
  105,1,Have you not considered how your Lord dealt with the People of the Elephant
  105,2,Did He not make their plan go wrong
  105,3,He sent against them swarms of birds
  105,4,Throwing at them rocks of baked clay
  105,5,Leaving them like chewed-up leaves
  106,1,For the security of Quraish
  106,2,Their security during winter and summer journeys
  106,3,Let them worship the Lord of this House
  106,4,"Who has fed them against hunger, and has secured them against fear"
  107,1,Have you considered him who denies the religion
  107,2,It is he who mistreats the orphan
  107,3,And does not encourage the feeding of the poor
  107,4,So woe to those who pray
  107,5,Those who are heedless of their prayers
  107,6,Those who put on the appearance
  107,7,And withhold the assistance
  108,1,We have given you plenty
  108,2,So pray to your Lord and sacrifice
  108,3,He who hates you is the loser
  109,1,"Say, 'O disbelievers"
  109,2,I do not worship what you worship
  109,3,Nor do you worship what I worship
  109,4,Nor do I serve what you serve
  109,5,Nor do you serve what I serve
  109,6,"You have your way, and I have my way"
  110,1,"When there comes God's victory, and conquest"
  110,2,And you see the people entering God's religion in multitudes
  110,3,"Then celebrate the praise of your Lord, and seek His forgiveness. He is the Accepter of Repentance"
  111,1,"Condemned are the hands of Abee Lahab, and he is condemned"
  111,2,"His wealth did not avail him, nor did what he acquired"
  111,3,He will burn in a Flaming Fire
  111,4,And his wife—the firewood carrier
  111,5,Around her neck is a rope of thorns
  112,1,"Say, 'He is God, the One"
  112,2,"God, the Absolute"
  112,3,"He begets not, nor was He begotten"
  112,4,And there is nothing comparable to Him
  113,1,"Say, 'I take refuge with the Lord of Daybreak"
  113,2,From the evil of what He created
  113,3,And from the evil of the darkness as it gathers
  113,4,And from the evil of those who practice sorcery
  113,5,And from the evil of an envious when he envies
  114,1,"Say, 'I seek refuge in the Lord of mankind"
  114,2,The King of mankind
  114,3,The God of mankind
  114,4,From the evil of the sneaky whisperer
  114,5,Who whispers into the hearts of people
  114,6,From among jinn and among people